SIMPLE: regality
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Regality
<hw>Re*gal"i*ty</hw> <pr>(r?*g?l"?*t?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>regalitas</ets>, from L. <ets>regalis</ets> regal, royal. See
<er>Regal</er>, and cf. <er>Royality</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Royalty; sovereignty; sovereign
jurisdiction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Passion] robs reason of her due <qex>regalitie</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He came partly in by the sword, and had high courage in all points
of <qex>regality</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An ensign or badge of royalty.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Regally</ent>⟦br⟧
